<br>
There are many many very valid reasons from game design, class balance, to individual player playing time restrictions which come to play on my opinion in this regard. <br>
<br>
Game design and lack of groupability forces many classes towards the solo line of playstyle. Now, exp allocation kicks all those people right square in the nuts....and will have the effect of making them play and level twice as long as they did before to make the same gains. Monks are caught up in this as well although we do not suffer from the lack of group friendliness that some classes do. <br>
<br>
And if that weren't enough, what about the player with restrictions on their playing time, they cannot with very good reason spend inordinate amounts of time looking for groups. This group has had sand kicked in it's face today. <br>
<br>
Verant took a laudable goal of giving people more exp for more risks taken and then proceeded to abort the whole fucking mess by introducing the low blue\light blue nerf. This is a classic case of knowing how to &quot;fuck up a wet dream.&quot; <br>
<br>
Grats VI.<br>
